@*
============================================================================
App.razor

Purpose: Root HTML template for the Blazor Server application
This is the entry point that wraps all Blazor components

Structure:
- HTML document shell (<!DOCTYPE>, <html>, <head>, <body>)
- CSS references (app.css, scoped styles)
- HeadOutlet for dynamic <head> content
- Routes component for page routing
- JavaScript files for Blazor framework and theme management

Render Mode: InteractiveServer
- All components run on the server, not in the browser
- User interactions sent to server via SignalR WebSocket connection
- Server sends UI updates back to browser
============================================================================
*@

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    @* UTF-8 character encoding for international characters (Hungarian text) *@
    <meta charset="utf-8" />

    @* Responsive design meta tag - enables mobile optimization *@
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    @* Base URL for relative paths - required for Blazor routing *@
    <base href="/" />

    @* Main application CSS styles *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="app.css" />

    @* Scoped component styles (auto-generated by Blazor) *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="WeatherDashboard.styles.css" />

    @* HeadOutlet: Allows components to inject content into <head> dynamically
        Example: PageTitle components add <title> tags here
        @rendermode="InteractiveServer" enables server-side rendering
    *@
    <HeadOutlet @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />
</head>

<body>
    @* Routes component: Renders the router and matched page components
        @rendermode="InteractiveServer" enables:
        - Server-side component execution
        - Real-time UI updates via SignalR
        - No need to download .NET runtime to browser
    *@
    <Routes @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />

    @* Blazor framework JavaScript - handles SignalR connection and DOM updates *@
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>

    @* Theme management JavaScript - initializes light/dark theme on page load *@
    <script src="js/theme.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
